&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-estoppel/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-estoppel/> ;
  schema:name "Estoppel" ;
  schema:description "An Estoppel is a quadruple (Q, R, ρ, δ) — a party Q whose position is being estopped, a relying party R who changed their position based on Q's prior representation ρ, and the detriment δ R would suffer if Q were now permitted to assert their actual position. The defining structure: estoppel does not extinguish Q's right (contrast with waiver) but blocks the path from Q's right C ∈ H_{t*} to the settled layer H*_{t*} within this forum — the forum's σ-nucleus refuses to process Q's claim because the contextual condition (R's reliance to their detriment) makes settlement of C inequitable. Formally: a nucleus-blocking condition imposed by the forum's site topology J — estoppel is a local sieve that prevents Q's claim from covering, not a retraction of the claim from the fiber." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:isPartOf &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/> ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-estoppel/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "Waiver, HohfeldianPosition, Standing, Authority, Breach, Contract, Norm, Culture" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-estoppel/> .

